"name_en":"Assessment, Community Alcohol\/Drug (Brief or Full)<br>Algoma Public Health",
"name_fr":"Assessment, Community Alcohol\/Drug (Brief or Full)<br>Algoma Public Health",
"description_en":"The program assists the residents of Algoma to achieve a life free from alcohol and\/or other drug related problems to individuals who are experiencing alcohol and\/or other drug related problems.\r\n\r\nBRIEF:\r\nMost often completed on computer. Group orientation\/education and brief assessment. The program provides an initial overview and education around alcohol and drugs and the healthy guidelines. Screening provides direction as to whether a full assessment is needed and\/or other group or individual treatment modalities. Subsequent appointments are assigned as necessary.\r\n\r\nFULL:\r\nThis is a confidential program for individuals, 12 years and older, who have alcohol and or other drug related problems. Social agency and other professional referrals are welcome. Alcohol\/drug assessment which includes individualized treatment plans and referrals to other programs and agencies; case management; counselling services; follow up services; relapse prevention; needle prevention and back on track program.",
