"description_en":"Court Support: The program offers support to people with mental illness\/addictions\/ intellectual disabilities who are in conflict with the law: General information is provided to the court re mental illness, services, and community resources.\r\n Dual Diagnosis Justice: Transitional case management, court support and release from custody planning to people with an intellectual disability or dual diagnosis.\r\n Release from Custody: Working closely with the medical unit at the Algoma Treatment and Remand Centre (ATRC) to provide mental health supports to individuals held in custody, including discharge planning re medication, finances, housing and referral in the community. It is recovery orientated and follows the principles of psychosocial rehabilitation. ",
