"name_en":"Counselling, Violence Against Women<br>Counselling Centre of East Algoma",
"name_fr":"Counseling, violence faite aux femmes<br>Centre de Counseling d'Algoma Est",
"description_en":"Program at CCEA provides advocacy and support to women who have been victims of abuse within their partner relationships. \r\n\r\nAbuse can be physical, emotional, sexual, and\/or financial. The goal of this program is to make our community safer for women and children, while fostering change initiated at the client's pace. \r\n\r\nIndividual Counselling is available to women aged 16+ who are living in, or have lived with abuse within an intimate relationship.\r\n\r\nGroup Counselling is offered\r\nWomen For Change - a 10-week group for women who have experienced abuse within an intimate relationship. Group focuses on education regarding abuse and hopes to increase the natural supports for participants (co-facilitated with staff from Maplegate). \r\n\r\nCreating Connections \u2013 aka the child witness to domestic violence group; a partnership between FLC, AFS, Maplegate, CAS & Mississauga Women\u2019s Shelter. Our portion of this program is focused on the delivery of the women\u2019s group.\r\n\r\nCommunity Lectures\r\nWe are building our capacity to deliver the Neighbours, Friends and Families campaign throughout East Algoma and will begin actively marketing this throughout our area in hopes of delivering as many presentations as possible. This effort is in partnership with Maplegate.\r\n\r\nOur Violence Against Women (VAW) counsellor will be offering educational presentations on a regular basis to residents of Maplegate (details yet to be finalized). ",
"description_fr":"Violence faite aux femmes assure la repr\u00e9sentation et le soutien des femmes qui ont subi de mauvais traitements dans une relation de couple. Ces mauvais traitements peuvent \u00eatre physiques, \u00e9motionnels, sexuels et\/ou financiers. Gr\u00e2ce \u00e0 notre partenariat avec les Services aux familles d'Algoma, nous sommes heureux de pouvoir proposer le groupe <<Cr\u00e9ons des connexions>> aux enfants t\u00e9moins de violence entre les adultes dont ils dependent.",
