"name_en":"Counselling Connect Services; Canadian Hearing Society; Health Promotion and Education",
"name_fr":"counseling CONNECT; Soci\u00e9t\u00e9 canadienne de l'ou\u00efe; Promotion de sant\u00e9 et \u00e9ducation",
"description_en":"Home visits available outside of Elliot Lake. Hearing Care Counselling Program and Hearing Aid Clinics held regularly. Call ahead for access to services below:\r\nConnect Counselling Services: Community-based program offering mental health, wellness and addiction services for the deaf, deafened and hard of hearing and their families. Support, education, advocacy, assessment, treatment, referral and counselling are offered as well. Model of service is matched to consumer needs. Fully accessible for Culturally Deaf, oral deaf, deafened and hard of hearing - use of american Sign Language (ASL), Langue Des Signs Quebecois (LSQ), interpreters, captions, technical devices, and video-conference for remote locations. Provides outreach and advocacy to culturally deaf, orally deaf and hard-of-hearing communities regarding mental health issues and how to access mainstream services. The program specializes in accessibility issues related to hearing loss ranging from profound deafness to mild hearing loss and the types of accessibility that will match the needs of each consumer.\r\ntag: senior",
"description_fr":"*Nous regrettons, mais ce contenu n'est pas encore disponible en fran\u00e7ais * Home visits available outside of Elliot Lake. Hearing Care Counselling Program and Hearing Aid Clinics held regularly. Call ahead for access to services below:\r\nConnect Counselling Services: Community-based program offering mental health, wellness and addiction services for the deaf, deafened and hard of hearing and their families. Support, education, advocacy, assessment, treatment, referral and counselling are offered as well. Model of service is matched to consumer needs. Fully accessible for Culturally Deaf, oral deaf, deafened and hard of hearing - use of american Sign Language (ASL), Langue Des Signs Quebecois (LSQ), interpreters, captions, technical devices, and video-conference for remote locations. Provides outreach and advocacy to culturally deaf, orally deaf and hard-of-hearing communities regarding mental health issues and how to access mainstream services. The program specializes in accessibility issues related to hearing loss ranging from profound deafness to mild hearing loss and the types of accessibility that will match the needs of each consumer.\r\ntag: a\u00een\u00e9",
