"name_fr":"Family and Community, Nog-Da-Win-Da-Min",
"description_en":"Serves as a mandated Native Child Welfare Prevention agency which ensures that Anishinawbek children, youth and families receive culturally appropriate services\r\n\r\n\u2022Created to follow a cultural service model of child protection services which involves parents, extended family members, Elders, community resource workers and First Nation leaders \r\n\u2022Delivers a full spectrum of culturally appropriate: prevention; early intervention; and child protection services\r\n\u2022Provides culturally-based education programs to communities on topics including domestic violence, parenting, life skills and self-esteem\r\n\r\nResponsible for the administration of the following programs and services: \r\n\u2022Alternative\/Foster Care (Genawenman Binojiuk) \r\n\u2022In-Home Support Program- in families where there is child maltreatment, skilled professionals can assist families to learn more appropriate ways to raise their children. \r\n\u2022Mino Madzwin Youth Program \r\n\u2022Prevention and Support Services - Workers will provide assistance and support to children and families to resolve child welfare crises and co-operatively plan and carry out actions designed to divert future, similar crises. All services are voluntary.",
