"name_en":"Timber Village Museum",
"name_fr":"Mus\u00e9e forestier Timber Village",
"description_en":"Timber Village Museum, owned and operated by the Town of Blind River, showcases the rich history and heritage of the people of Blind River and local North Channel Communities.\r\n\r\nOriginally built with the original artifacts from the McFadden Lumber Company, the museum houses a collection of lumbering and logging memorabilia, testament to the largest pine sawmill east of the Rocky Mountains.\r\n\r\nVisitors enjoy both indoor and outdoor exhibits, a variety of programs, changing local artist exhibitions as well as a fully stocked gift shop.\r\n\r\nVisit us in Blind River on Hwy 17, just east of the Northern Ontario Logging Memorial. Ample auto and bus parking, picnic area, and public washrooms are at the adjacent North Shore Travel Centre.\r\n\r\nMUSEUM ADMISSION RATES:\r\n$4\/Adult, $3\/Senior & Student; $1 Child 5 - 12; Under 5 Free; Family $10.\r\nPlease contact for group rates.\r\n\r\nMEMBERSHIP:\r\n$10\/individual; $18\/family; \r\n$25\/supporting* & $50\/patron*.\r\n*In addition to regular benefits of 10% discount in Gift Shop and free admission for one year, support and patron members receive a charitable tax receipt.",
"description_fr":"Situ\u00e9 \u00e0 c\u00f4t\u00e9 du Centre d\u2019information touristique de la Rive Nord, le Mus\u00e9e forestier Timber Village compte une collection d\u2019artefacts et d\u2019archives sur l\u2019histoire de la r\u00e9gion de Blind River, notamment sur l\u2019industrie foresti\u00e8re de la r\u00e9gion. Le site comprend aussi un galerie d\u2019art mettant en vedette l\u2019oeuvre d\u2019artistes et d\u2019artisans contemporains de la r\u00e9gion. On y organise des activit\u00e9s annuelles, dont la vente aux ench\u00e8res des cabanes d\u2019oiseaux au mois d\u2019avril, le pique-nique des oursons au mois d\u2019ao\u00fbt et la F\u00eate de la moisson au mois d\u2019octobre.",
