"description_en":"N\u2019Mninoeyaa Health Clinic Community Health Centre:\r\nNew patients must be Status, Non-Status, M\u00e9tis or family member of (e.g.. Child, spouse, common-law partner)\r\n\r\nPrenatal\/Nutrition:\r\nRestricted to families with who are prenatal.\r\n\r\nFamily Support:\r\nRestricted to families with children 6 months to 6 years of age\r\n\r\nHealthy Babies \/ Healthy Children:\r\nCan serve families with children 0-6 years of age.\r\n\r\nAkwe:go \r\nThis program has been specifically designed to provide a comprehensive program to urban Aboriginal children between the ages of 7-12.\r\n\r\nWasa Nabin \r\nThis program is geared to provide services to Urban Aboriginal Youth ages 13-18.\r\n\r\nAfter School \r\nThis program is part time and for grades 7 to 12.\r\n\r\nAlcohol & Drug Prevention\r\nThe alcohol & drug prevention program are available to assist people who are pursuing a drug and alcohol free life-style. \r\n\r\nAbinogii Kinomaago Daycare\r\nDaycare services to all children 18 months to 5 years. For information about the daycare, please do not hesitate to call - (705) 256-5634 ext. 2133. You may also visit the website click on Abinogii Kinomaago. If you are interested in putting your child on the waiting list, please visit www.saultdaycare.ca or call (705) 759-CARE (2273). \r\n\r\nOutreach\r\nFor people who are homeless or at risk of homelessness.\r\n\r\nHealing & Wellness\r\nFoster healing, reduce family violence and improve Aboriginal health. Weekly Sewing\/Drum circle\r\n\r\nLife Long\r\nClients must be deemed elderly frail, chronically ill and\/or disabled.\r\n\r\nApatisiwin Employment Unit\r\nOGI Programs serves urban Aboriginal people\r\nMTCU Employment Counsellor serve status people\r\n\r\nEducation Literacy & High School New or Returning Registrations\r\n\r\nMental Health Worker, Family Support, Family Support Assistant.\r\nCounselling & Cultural:\r\n \u00b7 Cultural Teachings \u00b7 Naming Ceremonies \u00b7 Sweat Lodge Ceremonies \u00b7 Wednesday nights \u00b7 Rides are provided from the Indian Friendship Centre \u00b7 If you wish to attend, please call on Tuesday\u2019s by 4:30pm, and \u00b7 Good Laughs.",
