"name_fr":"Literacy, Elliot Lake Learning Centre",
"description_en":"Offers literacy and basic skills training and academic upgrading to grade 8 (or LBS level 2) with certain exceptions up to grade 10. Our learning environment is highly supportive and we are somewhat more lenient with attendance than traditional schools, however, it is recommended that a learner not begin training until they are ready to make a consistent minimum commitment of 10 hours class time a week.\r\n\r\nHere is a list of some of the training on offer:\r\n\r\n\u2022 One-on-one tutoring for Independent Learning Credit subjects up to and including grade 10 with exceptions where appropriate\r\n\u2022 Upgrading of reading, writing and math skills up to and including grade 8\r\n\u2022 Hands-on basic orientation for cashier duties\r\n\u2022 Employment-specific modules for common jobs \r\n\u2022 Basic personal budgeting and money management\r\n\u2022 Basic computer skills oriented to employment ",
