"name_fr":"Mus\u00e9e des industries nucl\u00e9aire et mini\u00e8re d\u2019Elliot Lake",
"description_en":"The museum traces the history of the area from the lumbering and trapping days through the discovery of uranium mining, milling, and uses of uranium. It races the development of area mines, mine rescue and the development of the thriving modern community of Elliot Lake. It is also the home of the Canadian Mining Hall of Fame, which features the portraits and biographies of these who have made major contributions to the Canadian Mining Industry.\r\n\r\nDENISON DOORS\r\n\r\nThese doors once graced the main entrance to the Administration Building of the Elliot Lake Denison Mine, the world's largest uranium producing facility of its time. Graciously donated to the City of Elliot Lake, the doors are now a proud part of the Nuclear and Mining Museum display. The intricate design incorporates abstract impressions of atoms, machinery and equipment reminiscent of our mining era. On their own, each door is a masterpiece; in combination they are a unique work of art.\r\n\r\nFacilities: Gift Shop, washrooms, wheelchair accessible. Campground nearby.",
"description_fr":"Ce mus\u00e9e retrace l\u2019histoire de la r\u00e9gion \u00e0 partir des jours des b\u00fbcherons et des trappeurs jusqu\u2019\u00e0 la d\u00e9couverte de l\u2019extraction, le raffinage et l\u2019utilisation de l\u2019uranium. Il suit le d\u00e9veloppement des mines de la r\u00e9gion, les initiatives de sauvegarde des mines et le d\u00e9veloppement de la nouvelle communaut\u00e9 moderne et florissante d\u2019Elliot Lake. C\u2019est aussi le site du Temple de la renomm\u00e9e de l\u2019industrie mini\u00e8re canadienne, mettant en vedette, par des photos et biographies, les personnes qui ont contribu\u00e9 de fa\u00e7on importante \u00e0 l\u2019industrie mini\u00e8re au Canada.\r\n\r\nLes portes de Denison\r\n\r\nCes portes figuraient \u00e0 l\u2019entr\u00e9e principale de l\u2019\u00e9difice administratif de la mine Denison \u00e0 Elliot Lake, soit le plus important producteur d\u2019uranium dans le monde \u00e0 l\u2019\u00e9poque. G\u00e9n\u00e9reusement donn\u00e9es par la Ville d\u2019Elliot Lake, ces portes sont maintenant l\u2019un des points de mire du Mus\u00e9e des industries nucl\u00e9aire et mini\u00e8re. La cr\u00e9ation d\u00e9taill\u00e9e de ces portes incorpore des repr\u00e9sentations abstraites d\u2019atomes, de machines et d\u2019\u00e9quipement reli\u00e9s \u00e0 l\u2019industrie mini\u00e8re. Chaque porte est un chef-d\u2019oeuvre; la paire forme un objet d\u2019art unique.\r\n\r\nAutres services: boutique, salles de toilette, terrains de camping \u00e0 proximit\u00e9.",
