"name_en":"Rainbow Camp",
"name_fr":"Rainbow Camp",
"description_en":"WELCOME QUEER (LGBT+) AND ALLLIED YOUTH! AGES 13-17 Set in Northern Ontario amongst towering white pines on the shores of Lake Huron, Welcome Friends Camp for Youth\u009d (aka Rainbow Camp) is the perfect place to come OUT, make new friends and develop skills through traditional and non-traditional camp programming. Come to Camp where you: Have Fun! * Discover who you are & where you belong * Have fun with arts & crafts * Learn to relate with family and friends * Have fun swimming and canoeing * Deal with bullying and issues of self-esteem * Enjoy nature & the sand between your toes * Learn about gender, sexuality & health * Roast marshmallows over a campfire * Sing around a campfire * Enjoy home style meals * Experience a safe place to have fun * Live confidently and authentically * More than anything, this camp is a fun place for kids to ~COME OUT\u009d~ and be themselves! ",
